  <description type="morphology">Subshrubs, (1–)2–4(–5) × 3–8 dm. Stems: caudex absent; aerial flowering stems 0.2–0.6(–0.8) dm, floccose or tomentose, rarely glabrous. Leaf blade usually elliptic, (0.5–)1–2(–2.5) × (0.1–)0.2–0.6(–0.8) cm, densely to sparsely whitish-tomentose abaxially, less so to sparsely whitish-floccose adaxially, margins not revolute. Inflorescences (1–)2–4(–8) cm; branches floccose or glabrous. Involucres 2–3(–3.5) mm, subglabrous, glabrous, or merely floccose between angled ridges. Flowers 2–3 mm; perianth white to pink or rose. Achenes 2–3 mm.</description>
